<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1379">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/37.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 313,
                            of February 1 last, reporting your recent action in the matter of your
                            negotiations with the Panaman Government with a view to the
                            investigation of lie case of the riot on July 4 last in which certain
                            Americans were killed and wounded.</p>
                        <p>Your action in the matter is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>